            <who name="Simon Cope">copefamily</who>
            <bug_when>2007-01-18 14:22:15 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>changeValue is not triggered by DOM onchange event, rather focus/blur managed by Qx.  This is problematic when using non Qx widgets in the page as you don&#39;t get a changeValue event when focus goes to the other non-Qx widget (eg by clicking on the other widget).

You can hook onchange manually to work around it but there doesn&#39;t seem to be any reason for Qx not to use onchange.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>852</commentid>
            <who name="Sebastian Werner">info</who>
            <bug_when>2007-01-25 17:30:23 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Onchange triggers to often. (Creates too much overhead if there is a more complex action connected to the event). If you want to react on (direct) input changes you can use &quot;input&quot; as an alternative event. BTW: The blur/focus theory is often found in other toolkits, too.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
